// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/line/round-trip.test — `#line` round-trip golden
// per FR-035 + `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` §2.4 + the contract section
// "`#line` round-trip semantics (P13, FR-020, FR-021, FR-035)" in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Three input variants from `pp.ebnf §2.4`:
//   1. `#line <decimal-int>`
//   2. `#line <decimal-int> <string-literal>`
//   3. `#line <anything-else>` — macro-expanded; result MUST be
//      re-parsed as variant 1 or 2 (P13 emitter rule "always emit
//      the canonical form").
//
// Two canonical output forms (the only ones permitted to cross the
// seam):
//   1. `#line <decimal-int>`
//   2. `#line <decimal-int> <string-literal>`
//
// Round-trip invariants asserted here (per FR-035):
//   * Each input directive emits exactly one canonical `#line`
//     marker into the output stream (the lexer kind is
//     `tk_line_directive` — see test/lex/n5/line_marker.test).
//   * Subsequent tokens report post-`#line` virtual coordinates via
//     the `<virt-loc>` column of the `-emit=tokens` schema.
//   * Variant 3 input normalizes to variant 1 or 2 at the seam.
//
// We exercise variants **1 and 2** in this fixture. Variant 3 is
// covered by a separate `--check-prefix` block guarded by the
// implementer's variant-3 support state — the `nsl-frontend-impl`
// agent's Phase-4 work decides whether variant 3 is supported in
// this iteration. If variant 3 is deferred, the implementer
// removes the V3 RUN/CHECK block; doing so requires a contract
// amendment in `preprocessor-seam.contract.md` because P13's third
// variant is part of pp.ebnf §2.4 (the agent brief flagged this
// ambiguity for escalation).
//
// Tasks.md T050 + FR-035 + SC-003 + spec.md US2 acceptance scenarios
// 8 + 9.
//
// **RED state**: the unchanged Phase-3 lexer recognizes `#line`
// (per ecfee46) but does NOT update the SourceManager virtual-line
// table; <virt-loc> still reports the physical path. Phase-4 wires
// it through `SourceManager::addLineDirective()`.

// ---- VARIANT 1: `#line <decimal-int>` ------------------------------
// `#line 200` resets the line counter; the path stays as the
// physical temp-file path.
//
// RUN: echo '#line 200'      >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg v1_after;'  >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=V1

// V1: tk_line_directive
// V1: tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:2:1:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:200:1
// V1: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}v1_after{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:2:5:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:200:5

// ---- VARIANT 2: `#line <decimal-int> <string-literal>` -------------
// `#line 200 "alias.v"` resets BOTH the line counter and the virtual
// path. Subsequent <virt-loc> reports `alias.v:200:…`.
//
// RUN: echo '#line 200 "alias.v"' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg v2_after;'       >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=V2

// V2: tk_line_directive
// V2: tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:2:1:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}alias.v:200:1
// V2: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}v2_after{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:2:5:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}alias.v:200:5

// ---- VARIANT 3: `#line <anything-else>` (macro-expanded) -----------
// `#line %LN%` where `%LN%` macro-expands to `300 "macro.v"`. Per
// P13 emitter rule the OUTPUT is one canonical `#line 300
// "macro.v"` — the variant-3 form never crosses the seam.
//
// **Subject to P13 variant-3 support**: see contract section
// "Three input variants" — P13 mandates variant 3 normalization.
// If the parallel Phase-4 implementer chooses to defer variant 3,
// they must amend `preprocessor-seam.contract.md` and remove this
// block. Until then it stays.
//
// RUN: echo '#define LN 300 "macro.v"' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo '#line %%LN%%'             >> %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg v3_after;'            >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=V3

// V3: tk_line_directive
// V3: tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:3:1:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}macro.v:300:1
// V3: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}v3_after{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:3:5:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}macro.v:300:5
